@node Introduction "Introduction"
@{line}
@{jcenter}@{bg highlight}@{b} Introduction @{ub}@{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}

This archive simply contains some snapshots of my little Workbench, not
directly comparables with other which you can see on Aminet!@{line}

Well, I prefer to leave it simple, because I prefer functionality rather
estetic; but whit MagicWB icons it is nice ;-).@{line}

Actual resolution is 724x478x3, NTSC Hires Laced; to get this overscan
I changed the viewable area of monitor using his triggers.@{line}

If you have suggestions or else, contact the @{" author " link "author" 0}!@{line}

@endnode

@node Informations "Informations about my computer"
@{line}
@{jcenter}@{bg highlight}@{b} Informations about my computer @{ub}@{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}

Here's my computer specs:@{line}

Amiga 1200 Tower (built by me, so no Zorro slot :-( )@{line}
TQM with 68030 and 68882 at 50 MHz@{line}
16 MB Fast RAM and 2 MB Chip RAM@{line}
210 MB hard disk, I'll change it soon@{line}
Squirrel SCSI-II controller with 4x CD-ROM@{line}
Two DD drives@{line}
Modem 14.4k@{line}
Stero audio digitizer@{line}
An odd light pen@{line}
Scanner@{line}
9 pins color printer (Star LC-100)@{line}
1084S monitor - the worst thing in the whole system@{line}
Other CD-ROM Atapi 2x@{line}

In short:@{line}
A1200T/030/882/50/210HD/2DD/16FAST/2CHIP/SCSI-II/CD4x/CD2x/14.4k@{line}

I've also a basic Amiga 2000, with a bad CM8802 Philips monitor.@{line}

As you can see, I use WB in NTSC Hires >Lace< :-(

@endnode

